{{operational plan | name = Full Disclosure |partof=the [[Israel-Iran proxy conflict]] | image = [[File:Flickr - Israel Defense Forces - Operation Full Disclosure - Israel Navy Exposed Iranian Weapons Shipment to Gaza 001a.jpg|250px]] | caption = Official IDF photo showing operation ''Full Disclosure'' task force | scope = | planned = | planned_by = [[Israeli Navy]] | objective = Seize merchant vessel ''KLOS C'' | executed = 5 March 2014 | executed_by = [[Shayetet 13]], [[INS Hanit|INS ''Hanit'']], INS ''Hetz'' | outcome = Successful Israeli naval interception }} {{Shayetet 13 boardings}}
'''Operation ''Full Disclosure''''' ({{lang-he|מבצע חשיפה מלאה}}) was a military operation carried out by the [[Israel Defense Forces]] on March 5, 2014 in the [[Red Sea]].<ref name=idfblog>[http://www.idfblog.com/2014/03/05/operation-full-disclosure/ Operation Full Disclosure] - [[Israel Defense Forces]]</ref> After days of surveillance far out to sea, [[Israeli Navy]] [[Shayetet 13]] commandos seized the Iranian-owned and [[Panama|Panamanian]]-[[ship registration|registered]] [[merchant vessel]] ''[[Klos C]]'' that had set sail from [[Iran]], heading for [[Port Sudan]] via [[Iraq]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpost.com/Defense/Iranian-arms-vessel-captured-by-IDF-to-dock-in-Eilat-344702|title=Iranian arms vessel captured by IDF docks in Eilat|work=The Jerusalem Post - JPost.com|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> On board, the commandos found [[long-range missile]]s destined for [[Gaza Strip|Gaza]] concealed in [[wikt:container|containers]] full of Iranian bags marked as [[Portland cement]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4495859,00.html|title=Iran weapons ship: Behind the scenes of IDF 'Operation Full Disclosure'|work=ynet|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> An unnamed senior [[Egypt|Egyptian]] security official reportedly confirmed that the arms shipment was headed for militants in either Gaza or [[Sinai Peninsula|Sinai]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4496904,00.html|title=Egypt: Iranian arms ship destined for Sinai or Gaza|work=ynet|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> A UN panel of experts concluded that the weapons came from Iran and were being sent to Sudan, accusing Iran of violating the arms embargo.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jpost.com/Iranian-Threat/News/UN-experts-confirm-Arms-shipment-seized-by-Israel-in-March-came-from-Iran-360842|title=UN experts confirm: Arms shipment seized by Israel in March came from Iran|work=The Jerusalem Post - JPost.com|accessdate=19 December 2014}}</ref> [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 1929]] authorizes states to seize items, including arms, that Iran is forbidden from exporting.
The operation was led by Major General [[Ram Rothberg]], commander-in-chief of the Israel Navy, on board [[Sa'ar 5-class corvette]] [[INS Hanit|INS ''Hanit'']]. INS ''Hetz'', a [[Sa'ar 4.5-class missile boat]], also participated.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ynet.co.il/articles/0,7340,L-4495853,00.html|script-title=he:בראש הכוח עמדה אח"י חנית שנפגעה בלבנון|first=Yossi|last=Yehoshua|accessdate=September 27, 2014|date=March 6, 2014|newspaper=Ynet|language=Hebrew}}</ref>
