{{For|the 1920s sound-on-disc movie sound system|Photokinema}} {{anchor|world of imaging|imaging unlimited}} [[File:Z photokina Logo 4c.jpg|alt=|thumb|Photokina_Imaging Unlimited_logo]] [[Image:Südeingang Photokina.jpg|thumb|South Entrance of the [[Cologne Trade Fair]] during Photokina 2008.]]
'''Photokina''' (rendered in the promoters' branding as "photokina") is a [[trade fair]] held in Europe for the [[Photography|photographic]] and [[Reprography|imaging]] industries. It is the world's largest such trade fair.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} The first Photokina was held in [[Cologne]], [[Germany]], in 1950, and since 1966 it has been held biennially in September at the [[koelnmesse]] Trade Fair and Exhibition Centre in [[Deutz, Cologne|Deutz]]. The fair became an annual event starting in 2018, and will move to May starting in 2019.<ref name=Baskin>{{cite web|url=https://www.dpreview.com/news/7503898674/photokina-repositions-itself-will-become-an-annual-event |title=Photokina 'repositions' itself, will become an annual event |first=Dale |last=Baskin |publisher=''[[Digital Photography Review]]'' |date=May 23, 2017 |accessdate=May 30, 2017}}</ref> Many photographic and imaging companies introduce and showcase [[state of the art]] imaging products at Photokina.
==Similar trade shows== The show has two main competitors, both of which are annual shows held in different parts of the world. The CP+ show in [[Yokohama]], [[Japan]], originally the Japan Camera Show, has been held since the early 1960s. In the [[United States|U.S.]], the main photography show is [[Photo Marketing Association|PMA@CES]], which since 2012 has coincided with the [[Consumer Electronics Show]] in [[Las Vegas Valley|Las Vegas]].
==History== The first Photokina was held in 1950 at the initiative of {{Interlanguage link multi|Bruno Uhl|de}}. U.S. President [[Dwight D. Eisenhower]] sent a greeting [[telegram]] marking the opening of Photokina in 1956.{{citation needed|date=February 2018}} * The 2008 show featured 1,579 exhibitors from 46 countries and had over 169,000 visitors from 161 countries.<ref>[http://www.photokina-cologne.com/press/_press_information.php?aktion=pfach&p1id=kmpresse_photokinae&format=html&base=&tp=k2&search=&pmid=kmeigen.kmpresse_1222681963&start=0&anzahl=10&channel=kmeigen&language=e&archiv= photokina report 2008] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100226195218/http://www.photokina-cologne.com/press/_press_information.php?aktion=pfach&p1id=kmpresse_photokinae&format=html&base=&tp=k2&search=&pmid=kmeigen.kmpresse_1222681963&start=0&anzahl=10&channel=kmeigen&language=e&archiv= |date=February 26, 2010 }}</ref> * The 2010 Photokina took place from 21 to 26 September. It featured 1,251 suppliers from 45 countries and had over 180,000 visitors from 160 countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news-photokina.koelnmesse.info/2010/09/schlussbericht-photokina-2010-setzt-neue-massstaebe |title=photokina report 2010 |publisher=News-photokina.koelnmesse.info |access-date=2013-02-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724060337/http://news-photokina.koelnmesse.info/2010/09/schlussbericht-photokina-2010-setzt-neue-massstaebe/ |archivedate=2012-07-24 |df= }}</ref> * The number of visitors still increased to 185,000 from 166 countries for Photokina 2012, which took place from 18 to 23 September 2012 and hosted 1,158 suppliers from 41 countries.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.photokina.de/de/photokina/presse/presseinformationen/index.php?aktion=pfach&p1id=kmpresse_photokina&format=html&base=&tp=k3content&search=&pmid=kmeigen.kmpresse_1348390645&start=0&anzahl=10&channel=kmeigen&language=d |title=photokina report 2012 |publisher=photokina.de |date=2011-08-15 |access-date=2013-02-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150707143944/http://www.photokina.de/de/photokina/presse/presseinformationen/index.php?aktion=pfach&p1id=kmpresse_photokina&format=html&base=&tp=k3content&search=&pmid=kmeigen.kmpresse_1348390645&start=0&anzahl=10&channel=kmeigen&language=d |archivedate=2015-07-07 |df= }}</ref> The 2014 attendance remained roughly constant, at an estimated 185,000.<ref name="2014 report">{{cite press release |url=http://www.photokina.com/media/en/photokina/downloads_32/pdf_37/presse_1/schlussbericht.pdf |title=photokina 2014: Final Report |publisher=[[koelnmesse]] |date=2014-09-21 |access-date=2014-09-24 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140929015159/http://www.photokina.com/media/en/photokina/downloads_32/pdf_37/presse_1/schlussbericht.pdf |archivedate=2014-09-29 |df= }}</ref> The 2016 Photokina had about 191,000 visitors.<ref>http://www.photoscala.de/2016/09/26/rueckblick-das-war-die-photokina-2016/</ref> * Photokina 2018 was held in Cologne, Germany from 26 to 29 September 2018. The dates were originally announced as 25–30 September, but the format was shortened as a part of the change to an annual event.<ref name=Baskin/> *Photokina 2019, the first in the new annual cycle of events, will be held once again in Cologne, 8-11 May 2019.
